panels.description: The Largest Contentful Paint (LCP) metric reports the render time of the largest content element visible in the viewport.
panels.title: [Range] Largest Contentful Paint (LCP)

panels.description: The Speed Index is the average time at which visible parts of the page are displayed. It is expressed in milliseconds and dependent on size of the view port. It was created by Pat Meenan
panels.title: [Range] Speed Index

panels.description: Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS) measures the sum total of individual layout shift scores for the unexpected layout shift that occurs during maximum session window with 1 second gap, capped at 5 seconds. This is a Chrome only metric.

targets.query:
from(bucket: "sitespeed")
  |> range(start: v.timeRangeStart, stop: v.timeRangeStop)
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["_measurement"] == "firstContentfulPaint")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["_field"] == "max")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["browser"] =~ /^${browser:regex}$/)
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["category"] =~ /^${category:regex}$/)
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["project"] =~  /^${project:regex}$/)
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["connectivity"] == "native")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["group"] =~ /^${group:regex}$/)
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["origin"] == "browsertime")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["page"] =~ /^${page:regex}$/)
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["statistics"] == "googleWebVitals")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["summaryType"] == "pageSummary")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["testName"] =~ /^${testName:regex}$/)
  |> aggregateWindow(every: v.windowPeriod, fn: max, createEmpty: false)
  |> drop(columns: ["_field"])
  |> yield(name: "max")

import "regexp"
import "experimental"

normalizeTime = (t) => {
  normalized =
    if regexp.matchRegexpString(r: /[n|u|s|m|h|d|w|o|y]/, v: t) then experimental.addDuration(d: duration(v: t), to: now())
    else time(v: t)
  return normalized
}

historicalPeriod = -1d
historicalStart = experimental.addDuration(d: historicalPeriod, to: normalizeTime(t: string(v: v.timeRangeStart)))
historicalStop = experimental.addDuration(d: historicalPeriod, to: normalizeTime(t: string(v: v.timeRangeStop)))



from(bucket: "sitespeed")
  |> range(start: historicalStart, stop: historicalStop)
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["_measurement"] == "firstContentfulPaint")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["_field"] == "max")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["browser"] =~ /^${browser:regex}$/)
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["connectivity"] == "native")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["group"] =~ /^${group:regex}$/)
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["origin"] == "browsertime")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["page"] =~ /^${page:regex}$/)
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["statistics"] == "googleWebVitals")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["summaryType"] == "pageSummary")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["testName"] =~ /^${testName:regex}$/)
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["category"] =~ /^${category:regex}$/)
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["project"] =~  /^${project:regex}$/)
  |> aggregateWindow(every: v.windowPeriod, fn: max, createEmpty: false)
  |> timeShift(duration: - historicalPeriod, columns: ["_start", "_stop", "_time"])
  |> yield(name: "max")
